# Description
#     Here lie the mortal remains of the wmake build system.  This file prints
#     an error, partly as an attempt to re-train the muscle memory of OpenFOAM
#     veterans and partly as a grim memento mori for unmaintained build systems
#     everywhere.
#
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------

error=$(cat <<END

[==================================  Error  ===================================]

wmake support has been entirely removed from HELYX version 3.5.


To run HELYX, please source platforms/activeBuild.shrc.

(Note:  activeBuild.shrc points to the run-time settings for the latest build.
Specific builds can be sourced directly, e.g. by sourcing files like
"platforms/linux64GccDPInt32Opt.shrc").


To compile HELYX, please use the CMake build system.

For more information please see the compilation guide on the ENGYS portal
(www.engys.com) or contact support@engys.com.

[==============================================================================]
\n
END
)

echo -e "$error"
